    "text": "where without loss of generality we assume an-1 > an-2. By considering the pairs An-2, An and An-1, An-3 and using the trivial fact an > An-1, We deduce an-2 > An-3. We then compare the pairs an-4, an-2 and an-1, An-3, and using that an-1 > an-2, we deduce An-3 > An-4. Continuing in this fashion, we prove that an> an-1>... > a1 and so ak = k fork = 1,2,...,n, i.e. that the optimal arrangement is as claimed. In particular, the maximum value of the sum is",
