    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1996_Solutions_1996s_page_003_22",
    "text": "Conversely, any arrangement of dominoes where adjacent dominoes are separated by an even number of squares corresponds to a unique balanced string, once we choose whether the string starts with X or O. In other words, the number of balanced strings is twice the number of acceptable domino arrangements.",
